I read somewhere that one secret to business success is having a mentor or a business partner. I didn’t have the luxury of a teacher. And with regard to partners, well I do have my friends who are always supportive, but they didn’t share the business language so to speak, and so when it comes to the technicalities, I was on my own. At least that was how it was until I got the services of Braxton Yoeman from MySuccess.Team. He’s what they call a business coach. He helped me when I was developing new business ideas and like a partner, he pushed me to accomplishing my tasks and goals when I really needed pushing. He was instrumental in making me stay on track with my goals. As much as I want to take all the credit for my current success, the outcome would have probably been different had I done it alone. If you need help keeping your course in your business journey, get someone like Braxton Yoeman.

I’m from a family of proud entrepreneurs and self-made business men. They said my grandfather was a really talented salesman who could sell ice to Eskimos. My father made his fortune buying failing small businesses for cheap, rehabilitating them, and reselling them at a profit. My uncle owns a few car detailing shops, my aunt has several AirBnBs, my sister is an Amazon reseller, and my youngest brother is trading crypto currencies. Unfortunately, our family never shared trade secrets. Not in bad faith, of course. It’s just that we never were in the habit of mixing business stuff with family. And there’s also an assumption that money-making is second-nature to us and nobody in the family needed help with it. Until I did.  
I tried my hand at several business and all of them were dismal failures. I lost a lot of money and it made me seriously consider that I may have been adopted. But before surrendering my soul to a boring office job, I decided to take one last stab at it, both figuratively and literally. One of my interests is collecting ornamental hand-crafted knives, and to describe the new business briefly, I wanted to connect craftsmen with consumers. 
To do it differently this time, I got myself a business coach. One I got is Braxton Yoeman from MySuccess.team based on a few recommendations. Having a business coach was quite a revelation. Braxton really helped me formulate my business plans while providing insights that only an expert with true experience with business success will have. It’s like having a family member teaching me the ropes and guiding me along but without all the judgment perhaps.
Long story short, my members-only website for carvers and collectors is quite a hit with already a few hundred members. My site’s classifieds and online auctions are well participated and I’m getting a fair share of the profits and transaction fees. My family is impressed with me of course but I couldn’t tell them quite yet that I cheated a bit by hiring an exceptional business coach.

These people have provided stellar results to us and made sure that we reach our goals in the shortest time possible. I have been using their services for several months now, and my business has grown substantially. Highly recommended!
MySuccess.team and Braxton Yoeman are the secret to my new found success.

Good thing I came across this renowned business coach Braxton Yoeman. He gave me the confidence and clarity to realize the worth of what I am doing. He efficiently helped me to structure my business and within a month of working with him, I started getting new clients and my conversion rate has increased to 50%! That’s an amazing gain for me and my business! I can’t thank Braxton enough for all his help.

I was able to renew my motivation to act more towards my dreams and goals. It’s good to have you as a coach, Braxton!

I was so ready to give up on the business venture I started with my wife when we got married until a friend recommended me to get a business coach. MySuccess.Team assigned Braxton to me. Honestly, I was hesitant at first since I was not sure if it was a good investment. However, Braxton helped me with different aspects of my business that made my life easier. Now, I can be both a good father to my children and a successful businessman. Thanks to you!
